body:
According to the SystemVerilog specification grammar, the for loop initialization section (as well as the expression and step) should be optional as they are in C/C++.  So

```systemverilog
module ForInit;
    initial begin
        int i;
        i = 0;
        for (; i < 5; i++) begin
            $display("%1d",i);
        end
    end
endmodule
```
should be accepted, but 12.0 (devel) rejects it with "Incomprehensible for loop".

